"{\"uid\": \"salon.com-2024-07-26-so-metal-headless-marie-antoinette-steals-the-show-at-paris-olympics-opening-ceremony\", \"text\": \"In an interview withBritish Vogueramping up to theParis Olympicsopening ceremony on Friday,\\u00a0artistic director\\u00a0Thomas Jolly spoke of the Olympic ceremonies as being \\\"a celebration of being alive,\\\" but he managed to pull off a delightfully morbid - and extremely metal - production that paid bloody tribute to a historically famous dead lady, Marie Antoinette. A headless Marie Antoinette, to be more specific.  Aiming to\\u00a0\\\"play with\\\" but also \\\"challenge\\\" French clich\\u00e9 in the opening, he nailed the landing there,shocking someand delighting many others with whatVultureaptly describes in their coverage as \\\"a full musical, metal-opera-Cameron Mackintosh mash-up tribute to \\u2026 the guillotine,\\\" featuring \\\"decapitated faces painted clown-white [singing] the French revolutionary song \\\"\\u00c7a ira\\\" alongside the heavy-metal band Gojira\\\"\\u00a0- the first metal band to ever play at the Olympic Games - during\\u00a0the \\\"Libert\\u00e9\\\" portion of the ceremony.  The\\u00a0headless figures depicting the 18th century Queen Marie Antoinette performing along the Seine river embankment outside the Conciergerie, where the queen was held captive during the French Revolution, inspired CNN's Jake Tapper to do a funny little tweet in the key of Charli XCX, writing, \\\"Headless Marie Antoinette isbrat\\\" in a widely shared post to social media.  Headless Marie Antoinette is brathttps://t.co/MeBrLYT15S  - Jake Tapper \\ud83e\\udd85 (@jaketapper)July 26, 2024    Tough for evenCeline Dionto beat in her ceremony performance, I'd say.  Clips of the performance are beingrapidly yankedoff of X and YouTube, due to copyright, but you can see snippets of headless Marie Antoinette onTikTokand via small edits, like the one below:  Copyright \\u00a9 2025 Salon.com, LLC. Reproduction of material from any 